@prefix : <https://www.somusicvocabulary.org/music#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

# NEGATIVE: :RoleBearerShape — a band does not conduct.
#
# Demoting the role classes threw away the one thing subclassing gave for free. Under the old
# model `:Conductor ⊑ :Musician ⊑ gist:Person` guaranteed a conductor was a PERSON without
# anyone having to state it. gist is explicit that a Category carries "no formal semantics",
# so every guarantee the subclass axioms used to make has to be restated in SHACL — and this
# one was not. :hasRole has rdfs:domain :MusicalAgent, which admits :Band, so a band could
# hold :ConductorRole and nothing objected.

:NEG_ConductingBand a :RockBand ;
    rdfs:label "Negative fixture — a band that claims to conduct"@en ;
    :hasRole :ConductorRole ;
    .

:ConductorRole a :MusicalRole .
